The paper discusses the effects of fractional power control on the downlink performance of massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The study also considers different deployment-related parameters, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The simulations are based on a spatial channel model, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR).
